                     <title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Ḥeleḳ ha-diḳduḳ</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <title xml:lang="he">חלק הדקדוק</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <author>
                        
                        
                        
                        <persName xml:lang="en" key="viaf.org/viaf/97265866">Ṣaliḥ, Yaḥyā ben Joseph, 1725-1806</persName>
                        
                        
                        
                        <persName xml:lang="he" key="viaf.org/viaf/97265866">צאלח, יחיא בן יוסף, 1725-1806</persName>
                     
                     
                     
                     </author>
                     
                     
                     
                     <note>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>Contains a series of masoretic statements on the biblical books, with frequent references to the Targum, Rashi, Bahya ibn Pakuda, and other authors. </p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>The work is preceded by: kabalistic notes (folio 1r), an alphabetical piece in Aramaic (folio 1v), a preface (folio 2r), a poem in Aramaic (folio 3r), a communication in Arabic regarding the copying of the manuscript (folio 5v). The work itself begins on folio 6r. There are additional pieces following on folios 40v-43r.</p>
                     
                     
                     
                     </note>
                  
                  
                  
                  </msItem>
               
               
               
